// An out-of-order event in a hopping configuration is delivered to every target
// window that is still open and silently skipped for those that have already
// closed. With size=3s, every=1s and the default lag tolerance, the clock
// reaches 5s before the event at 3s arrives: its windows [1s, 4s) and [2s, 5s)
// have closed and are skipped, while [3s, 6s) still receives it. Because the
// event reaches at least one open window, it is not reported as fully dropped.
from {ts: 0s.from_epoch(), v: "x"},
     {ts: 5s.from_epoch(), v: "y"},
     {ts: 3s.from_epoch(), v: "z"}
window size=3s, every=1s, on=ts {
  summarize vals=collect(v)
  start = $window.start.since_epoch()
}
sort start
